@startuml Data Flow Diagram for PayMate

!theme vibrant

title Data Flow Diagram (Level 0) - PayMate Web App

' Define Actors (External Entities)
actor "User" as User
actor "Payment Gateway" as PaymentGateway
actor "AI Service" as AIService

' Define the System Boundary
rectangle "PayMate Web App" as System {
    ' Define Processes within the system
    (1.0\nHandle Authentication) as Auth
    (2.0\nProcess Payment) as ProcessPayment
    (3.0\nProvide AI Assistance) as AIAssistance
    (4.0\nDisplay Information) as DisplayInfo

    ' Define Data Stores (conceptual for this prototype)
    database "User Credentials\n(Local Storage)" as UserStore
    database "Transaction History\n(Mock Data)" as TransactionStore
}


' Data Flows

' User Authentication Flow
User -->> Auth : Login/Signup Credentials
Auth -->> UserStore : Store/Verify Credentials
UserStore -->> Auth : User Data
Auth -->> User : Authentication Status

' Payment Flow
User -->> ProcessPayment: Payment Details (Amount, Recipient)
ProcessPayment ->> PaymentGateway : Payment Request
PaymentGateway ->> ProcessPayment : Transaction Status (Mocked)
ProcessPayment ->> TransactionStore : Record Transaction
ProcessPayment ->> User : Payment Confirmation

' Information Display Flow
User ->> DisplayInfo : Request Dashboard/History
TransactionStore -> DisplayInfo : Transaction Data
DisplayInfo ->> User : Rendered UI (Balance, History)

' AI Assistance Flow
User ->> AIAssistance : Support Query / Dashboard Load
AIAssistance ->> AIService : Prompt (Query / Transaction Data)
AIService ->> AIAssistance : AI Response (Chat Reply / Suggestions)
AIAssistance ->> DisplayInfo : Suggestions for Dashboard
AIAssistance ->> User : AI Chat Response


@enduml
